Subject: RE: [T2] Oli pressure switch light still on

Not sure, but that wire may not go directly to the
dashboard...it may go through the engine wire harness,
through a connector, to another harness up front.

If you have a manual, look up the wiring diagram...it
should tell you the color code for the wire that
actually connects to the dash light.

At one point I ran a bundle of 5-6 wires from the
engine to the dash for my oil pressure and temp
guages...this leaves me a few extra wires for future
applications and for this sort of trouble-shooting.


